Package com.github.cwilper.ttff

Useful abstractions for working with object sequences.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Closeable An object that must be closed when no longer in use.
Filter<T> A function that accepts, rejects, or transforms objects.
Sink<T> A receiver of objects.
Source<T> A sequence of objects.
 

Class Summary
AbstractFilter<T> Convenience base class for Filter implementations.
AbstractSink<T> Convenience base class for Sink implementations.
AbstractSource<T> Convenience base class for Source implementations.
Filters Static utility methods for creating common types of Filters.
Sources Static utility methods for creating, filtering, and draining Sources.
